# Security Rules

## API keys and secrets
- NEVER ask Kyle to paste API keys, tokens, passwords, or other secrets directly into chat
- When walking through CLI commands that include secrets (e.g. `supabase secrets set`),
  use `YOUR_KEY_HERE` placeholder text and tell Kyle to substitute locally
- After Kyle runs a command containing a secret, instruct him to redact the secret
  before pasting any command output back into chat
- If a secret accidentally appears in chat output, immediately tell Kyle to revoke
  and rotate that secret before continuing

## Environment variables
- Secrets used by the React Native app live in `.env` at project root
  (already gitignored)
- Secrets used by Supabase Edge Functions live in Supabase Secrets, set via:
  `supabase secrets set NAME=value`
- The Anthropic API key lives in Supabase Secrets ONLY — never in `.env`,
  never in app code, never in the bundle
- The `EXPO_PUBLIC_` prefix means a variable WILL be bundled into the app
  and exposed on the device. Never use this prefix for secret values

## Edge Function pattern
- All third-party API calls that require secret keys go through Supabase
  Edge Functions, never direct calls from the client
- The phone calls Supabase using the anon key (safe to ship)
- Supabase calls third-party APIs using its server-side secrets

## Git
- Confirm `.env` and `.env.local` are in `.gitignore` before any commit
- If a secret was ever committed (even briefly), assume it is compromised
  and rotate it immediately